Data sets for examples; adapted from bciex::bci12vft_mini.

top4quad

top1quad

Format

An object of class tbl_df (inherits from tbl, data.frame) with 964 rows and 28 columns.

Examples

library(dplyr)
#> 
#> Attaching package: ‘dplyr’
#> The following object is masked from ‘package:fgeo.map’:
#> 
#>     collapse
#> The following objects are masked from ‘package:stats’:
#> 
#>     filter, lag
#> The following object is masked from ‘package:testthat’:
#> 
#>     matches
#> The following objects are masked from ‘package:base’:
#> 
#>     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
all_quad <- bciex::bci12vft_mini %>%
  dplyr::rename(QX = x, QY = y) %>%
  dplyr::filter(PlotID == 1) %>%
  fgeo.tool::top(CensusID)

top4quad <- all_quad %>% fgeo.tool::top(QuadratID, 4)
identical(top4quad, fgeo.map::top4quad)
#> [1] TRUE

top1quad <- all_quad %>% fgeo.tool::top(QuadratID, 1)
identical(top1quad, fgeo.map::top4quad)
#> [1] FALSE
